{0 Test Code Block Handlers}

This page tests code block metadata preservation and handler infrastructure.

{1 Basic Code Block}

A simple code block with just a language tag:

{@ocaml[
let x = 1
]}

{1 Code Block with Metadata}

A code block with key=value bindings:

{@ocaml env=test version=5.0[
let y = 2
]}

{1 Code Block with Bare Tags}

A code block with bare tags (boolean flags):

{@ocaml skip noeval[
let z = 3
]}

{1 Code Block with Mixed Tags}

A code block with both bindings and bare tags:

{@python version=3.11 async highlight[
def hello():
    print("Hello")
]}

{1 Graphviz DOT Diagrams}

Client-side rendering (default) with Viz.js:

{@dot[
digraph G {
  a -> b -> c;
  b -> d;
}
]}

With layout and dimensions:

{@dot layout=neato width=400px[
graph G {
  a -- b -- c -- a;
}
]}

Server-side PNG rendering (requires graphviz installed):

{@dot format=png filename=my-graph.png[
digraph Dependencies {
  rankdir=LR;
  A [label="Module A"];
  B [label="Module B"];
  C [label="Module C"];
  A -> B -> C;
}
]}

Server-side SVG rendering:

{@dot format=svg layout=circo[
digraph Circular {
  a -> b -> c -> d -> e -> a;
}
]}

{1 Mermaid Diagrams}

Client-side rendering (default) with Mermaid.js:

{@mermaid[
graph LR
  A[Start] --> B{Decision}
  B -->|Yes| C[OK]
  B -->|No| D[Cancel]
]}

With theme option:

{@mermaid theme=forest[
sequenceDiagram
  Alice->>Bob: Hello
  Bob-->>Alice: Hi
]}

Server-side PNG rendering (requires mmdc/mermaid-cli installed):

{@mermaid format=png theme=neutral[
pie title Pets
  "Dogs" : 386
  "Cats" : 85
  "Birds" : 15
]}

Server-side SVG with custom filename:

{@mermaid format=svg filename=class-diagram.svg[
classDiagram
  Animal <|-- Duck
  Animal <|-- Fish
  Animal : +int age
  Animal : +String gender
  Animal: +isMammal()
  Duck : +String beakColor
  Duck : +swim()
  Fish : +int sizeInFeet
  Fish : +canEat()
]}

{1 Message Sequence Charts}

Client-side rendering (default) with mscgen-inpage.js:

{@msc[
msc {
  a, b, c;
  a -> b [label="request"];
  b -> c [label="forward"];
  c -> b [label="response"];
  b -> a [label="reply"];
}
]}

With named style and dimensions:

{@msc named-style=lazy width=500px[
msc {
  client, server, database;
  client -> server [label="HTTP GET"];
  server -> database [label="SELECT"];
  database -> server [label="rows"];
  server -> client [label="JSON"];
}
]}

Server-side PNG rendering (requires mscgen installed):

{@msc format=png[
msc {
  Alice, Bob, Carol;
  Alice -> Bob [label="Hello"];
  Bob -> Carol [label="Hi there"];
  Carol -> Alice [label="Greetings"];
}
]}

Server-side SVG with custom filename:

{@msc format=svg filename=protocol.svg[
msc {
  sender, receiver;
  sender -> receiver [label="SYN"];
  receiver -> sender [label="SYN-ACK"];
  sender -> receiver [label="ACK"];
  --- [label="connection established"];
  sender -> receiver [label="DATA"];
  receiver -> sender [label="ACK"];
}
]}
